<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Mix sugar, sugar syrup, milk, coarse salt in a bowl.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Melt the butter, then add the sugar and milk mixture. Keep stirring constantly on high heat until the caramel is thick and light brown.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Off the heat carefully add the double cream to the caramel]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Line a baking pan with buttered foil, and pour the caramel in. Let cool until until firm enough to cut. Put in the fridge if not hard enough, about  3-4 hr]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Put the dark chocolate, butter in a bowl and put the bowl over a pot with boiling water. Melt until smooth]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Beat together sugar, eggs, egg yolks in a bowl until thick]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the butter and chocolate mixture ]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add the flour, pinch of salt, and vanilla seeds and beat until well mixed and solid flour, vanilla pod]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Cut the solid caramel into 8 cubes. Split the cake mixture into 8 ramekins, and wedge a caramel cube in the middle of each ]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Bake for 14-16m at 180Â°. Let cool for 4 mins before tipping on a plate and sprinkle icing sugar over the brownies. ]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
